    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It turns out that \"Fiat-Shamir protection\" is not necessary if we just commit to the crosslink (and in phase 1 persistent) committee directly. A block at time T would commit to the crosslink committee at time T + 4 epochs, and to the persistent committee at time T + 9 days, so you can just hop forward through the \"use a Merkle path from a block to determine the public keys for a future block, verify the signature of the future block, repeat\" technique. This is good news because it really reduces the complexity of a light client; we're talking about ~200 kb per ~9 days in the worst case, and there's ways to improve on those numbers.",
